      "why_text": "The 2026 World Cup is being dubbed the first 'AI World Cup,' and the numbers are staggering \u2014 $11 billion in projected economic activity driven in part by how AI is reshaping everything from ticketing and logistics to broadcast and fan engagement. This isn't just a sports story; it's a stress test for whether mega-events can actually deliver on their economic promises in an era of inflation, host-city skepticism, and algorithmic everything. The tension between the headline number and real local economic struggles on the ground is the story underneath the story.",
