      "why_text": "At 32, this former teacher ditched the classroom to co-found a fidget toy business with her father \u2014 and last year it pulled in $428,000, making it a sharp case study in the post-pandemic pivot economy. The story lands at the intersection of two big cultural currents: the ongoing exodus from underpaid teaching jobs and the sustained, quietly massive market for sensory and focus toys that never really faded after the spinner craze. It's a reminder that 'small product' businesses built on real consumer need \u2014 not hype \u2014 can quietly generate serious money.",
